    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><persName>Judah's</persName> Death</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Phila</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>May 31st</date>
                <add>?</add>
            </p>
            <p>My dear <addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your pens are execrable<add>?</add><lb/> &amp; I can scarcely write
                with them.<lb/> Your letter of the <date>30th</date> had just<lb/> been received;
                Mamma says<lb/> that she thinks “<persName>Mr. <hi rend="underline"
                    >Judah's</hi></persName><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">Will is shameful &amp; she never</hi><lb/> heard of anything so
                unjust.”<lb/> We are sorry to hear that you<lb/> have caught another cold, you<lb/>
                should be more careful.<lb/> Two more letters have been re-<lb/>ceived from
                    <persName>Mr. M. M. Allen</persName>; in<lb/> one of them he wished to know<lb/>
                whether you intended leaving<lb/> town this week, &amp; desired to know<lb/>
                immediately, as otherwise he would<lb/> not come here to read on
                    <date>Saturday</date><lb/> so I wrote him a few lines telling<lb/> him that you
                had gone, I</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>suppose that it will be all right<lb/> Mamma took the note herself, &amp;<lb/> handed
                it to <persName>Mr. A. T. Jones</persName> at his<lb/> office, &amp; then she went
                to see the<lb/> girls &amp; found them looking very<lb/> well; they send their love
                to you.<lb/> There are letters here from <persName>Mr<lb/> Allen</persName>,
                    <persName>Mr M. Isaacs</persName>, <persName>Mr Louis<lb/> Solomon</persName>
                &amp; <persName>J. N. Cardozo</persName>.</p>
            <p><persName>Mr Allen</persName> sends a copy of the<lb/> proceedings of the “Board of
                dele-<lb/>gates”. <persName>Mr. Isaacs</persName> officially<lb/> informs you that
                you were<lb/> unanimously reelected Vice Presi-<lb/>dent; <persName>Mr
                    Hart</persName> was chosen President<lb/> in place of <persName>Judge
                    Cardozo</persName> who<lb/> was absent &amp;c. A resolution<lb/> was unanimously
                adopted to<lb/> the effect that the absence of<lb/>
                <persName>Rev I. Leeser</persName> occasioned by the<lb/> death of a relative, was
                deeply<lb/> regretted by the <sic>conreation</sic><add>?</add>.<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Louis Solomon</persName>, <placeName>Southfield Ogn.</placeName><lb/>
                wishes to know the price of the<lb/> “Family Bible,” also the price of<lb/> a <hi
                    rend="underline"><add>?</add> sett</hi> of prayers according</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>to the German minhag, English<lb/> &amp; Hebrew; he encloses a stamp<lb/> so I intend
                to send him an<lb/> answer, but your sets of prayers<lb/> are all Portuguese.</p>
            <p><persName>Mr Cardoza</persName> sends an advertise-<lb/>ment for the “Occident.”</p>
            <p>This is all I believe.</p>
            <p>If you wish it I can send you<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Isaac's</persName> letter when I <add>?</add>,<lb/> unless you fear it
                may get lost.<lb/>
                <persName>Aunt &amp; Uncle <add>?</add>ash</persName> are coming<lb/> today so I
                shall not have much<lb/> time to translate, &amp; more over it<lb/> is <hi
                    rend="underline">awfully hard <sic>german</sic></hi>.<lb/> Things go on here as usual.<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Jones</persName>' son called for the<lb/> books. The large Bible for<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline"><add>?</add></hi>, has been sent here;<lb/> what is to be done
                with it?<lb/> Mamma's eyes trouble her very<lb/> much, but she looks<add>?</add>
                better to-<lb/>day.</p>
            <p>We received a letter from <persName>Uncle Sam</persName><lb/> on <date>Monday</date>;
                they are all well with</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>the exception of <persName>Mary<add>?</add></persName> who is<lb/> again sick.</p>
            <p><persName>Jesse Nashes<add>?</add></persName> wife, <persName>Clara</persName>,
                is<lb/> dead; she died last <date>Tuesday</date><lb/> is it not very sad?</p>
            <p>This letter is <add>?</add> so good bye<lb/> Mama &amp; <persName>Delia</persName>
                send Love &amp;<lb/> a <hi rend="underline">little <add>?</add></hi> comes from</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">L. L. Lazarus</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Write soon</p>
        </body>
